##### MF33: COVARIANCES OF NEUTRON CROSS SECTIONS                 1031 1451
                                                                  1031 1451
In MF33, we store the covariances of most, but not all, reaction  1031 1451
channels that are given in MF3. All covariances are generated     1031 1451
with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates TALYS runs using    1031 1451
a Monte Carlo parameter method.                                   1031 1451
For each MT-number, the information consists of:                  1031 1451
1. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Ea (variances)                1031 1451
2. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Eb (correlations for the      1031 1451
   same reaction channel between different energies)              1031 1451
3. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Ea (correlations between      1031 1451
   different reaction channels for the same energy)               1031 1451
4. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Eb (correlations between      1031 1451
   different reaction channels for different energies)            1031 1451
Classes 1 and 2 are covered by NI-type subsubsections with        1031 1451
flag LB=5, followed by a LB=8 section which contains              1031 1451
the cross section variances multiplied by 1.e-3. Next, classes 3  1031 1451
and 4 are covered by flag LB=6 to account for the different       1031 1451
energy grids that two correlating MT-sections may have. Since     1031 1451
the total correlation matrix is fully symmetric, we only need to  1031 1451
include the correlation elements between different MT-numbers     1031 1451
once, and we do that in the subsection with the lowest of the     1031 1451
two MT-numbers. We include covariance information for all the     1031 1451
total cross sections, the lumped partial cross sections and the   1031 1451
individual inelastic cross sections per level (MT51,...). We do   1031 1451
not include covariances for MT600 and higher MT-numbers. For the  1031 1451
most important channels, we include cross-channel correlations.   1031 1451
                                                                  1031 1451
##### MF34: COVARIANCES OF ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS                  1031 1451
                                                                  1031 1451
In MF34, we store the covariances of the elastic scattering       1031 1451
angular distributions that are given in MF4/MT2. All covariances  1031 1451
are generated with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates       1031 1451
TALYS runs using a Monte Carlo parameter method. The tables are   1031 1451
restricted to MT2 and contain covariances for the first 6         1031 1451
Legendre coefficients. Both intra- and inter-correlations of the  1031 1451
various Legendre coefficients are given. As in MF33, the LB5      1031 1451
representation is used.                                           1031 1451
                                                                  1031 1451
##### MF40: COVARIANCES OF ISOMER PRODUCTION                      1031 1451
